io.github.goodees.ese.core.dispatch

Class Dispatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.goodees.ese.core.dispatch.Dispatcher

  • public class Dispatcher
extends Object
    Asynchronous message dispatcher. Guarantees to handle at most one message at time per entity. Internally, the dispatcher maintains a queue of invocations for every entity id. Whenever a new request should be invoked, the dispatcher checks if it is not invoking a request already.

      • execute

        public <R extends Request<RS>,RS> CompletableFuture<RS> execute(String id,
                                                                R request)
        Schedule a request. The request is added to entity's mailbox, and that mailbox is scheduled for dequeue. The response is returned immediately, as it is just a holder for future result that completes when the the request invocation completes.
        Type Parameters:
        R - type of request
        RS - type of response
        Parameters:
        id - entity id
        request - request to pass
        Returns:
        the promise for the response
